        <span>MTG Auto Deck</span>
      </a>
      <nav class="nav-actions" aria-label="Account links">
        <a
          class="text-link github-link"
          href={githubUrl}
          aria-label="GitHub"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer"
        >
          <svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" aria-hidden="true">
            <path
              d="M8 0C3.58 0 0 3.58 0 8c0 3.54 2.29 6.53 5.47 7.59.4.07.55-.17.55-.38 0-.19-.01-.82-.01-1.49-2.01.37-2.53-.49-2.69-.94-.09-.23-.48-.94-.82-1.13-.28-.15-.68-.52-.01-.53.63-.01 1.08.58 1.23.82.72 1.21 1.87.87 2.33.66.07-.52.28-.87.51-1.07-1.78-.2-3.64-.89-3.64-3.95 0-.87.31-1.59.82-2.15-.08-.2-.36-1.02.08-2.12 0 0 .67-.21 2.2.82A7.64 7.64 0 0 1 8 3.86c.68 0 1.36.09 2 .27 1.53-1.04 2.2-.82 2.2-.82.44 1.1.16 1.92.08 2.12.51.56.82 1.27.82 2.15 0 3.07-1.87 3.75-3.65 3.95.29.25.54.73.54 1.48 0 1.07-.01 1.93-.01 2.2 0 .21.15.46.55.38A8.01 8.01 0 0 0 16 8c0-4.42-3.58-8-8-8Z"
            />
          </svg>
        </a>
        <a class="text-link" href={signInUrl}>Log in</a>
        <a class="button button-secondary" href={signUpUrl}>Sign up</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main class="article-page">
      <article class="article-shell" aria-labelledby="article-title">
        <h1 id="article-title">{title}</h1>
        <p class="article-date">{date}</p>

        <section class="benchmark-chart-section">
          <h2 class="benchmark-chart-heading">
            Overall Score
            <span>(higher is better) - click on bar to view simulations</span>
          </h2>
          <div
            class="benchmark-chart-viewport"
            data-mtg-bench-chart-viewport
          >
            <div
              class="benchmark-score-chart benchmark-chart-scale-frame"
              data-mtg-bench-score-chart
              role="group"
              aria-label="MTG Auto Deck benchmark scores"
            ></div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="benchmark-chart-section">
          <h2 class="benchmark-chart-heading">
            Cost vs Score
            <span>- click on point to view simulations</span>
          </h2>
          <div
            class="benchmark-chart-viewport"
            data-mtg-bench-chart-viewport
          >
            <div
              class="benchmark-scatter-chart benchmark-chart-scale-frame"
              data-mtg-bench-cost-score-chart
              role="group"
              aria-label="Cost per attempted turn from $0.00 to $0.30 versus Overall Score from 0 to 100"
            ></div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <div class="article-body">
          <section class="article-body-section">
            <h2>How the benchmark works</h2>
            <p>
              The main idea is that if an LLM is smart enough to play good magic, then it is also smart enough to not need a rules engine.
              A rules engine that enforces legal actions would improve the performance floor, but I don't think it would improve the overall quality of the simulation.
            </p>
            <p>
              Each LLM call has access to an MCP server with primitive library operations. It can do things like draw a card from the top of the deck, return card to bottom of deck, and shuffle.
              To simulate more advanced operations, like
              <a
                href="https://mtg.fandom.com/wiki/Scry"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noreferrer noopener">scry</a
              >
              or
              <a
                href="https://mtg.fandom.com/wiki/Surveil"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noreferrer noopener">surveil</a
              >,
              it can use multiple library tool calls.
            </p>
            <p>
              Everything other than the library is managed by the LLM. Legality checks and scoring for the benchmarks was all done with gpt-5.5 (medium).
              From my testing, LLMs were much better at evaluating if a simulated turn was legal than they were at actually performing a legal turn simulation.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="article-body-section">
            <h2>Why I choose to use an MCP server</h2>
            <p>
              I have full control over all of the data and the LLM api calls, so why use MCP instead of basic function/tool calling?
            </p>
            <p>
              The main reason is that OpenAI and Anthropic allow you to provide a remote MCP server url in an api request.
              This means that OpenAI or Anthropic handle the agent loop. This has two major benifits.
            </p>
            <ol>
              <li>Since it is one api call, you don't pay for the cached input token cost after each tool use (at least with OpenAI. more on that later)</li>
              <li>You can use the batch api for 50% savings without having to submit a new batch after every tool call</li>
            </ol>
          </section>

          <section class="article-body-section">
            <h2>Input token caching</h2>
            <p>
              In my opinion, the way cached input tokens are charged does not make sense for agent loops. The pricing makes sense for independent requests.
              If multiple independent api calls start with the same large system prompt, input caching gets you a discount for free, or for a small caching fee.
            </p>
            <p>
              With an agent loop, however, you are charged the cached input cost for a large system prompt after every tool call.
              Consider an example. Assume the system prompt is already cached and tool calls result in negligible token use.
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Large system prompt = 10k tokens</li>
              <li>Agent calls 10 tool functions (not parallel)</li>
              <li>Billed cached input tokens = 10k + 10k * 10 = 110k tokens</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              I don't think it makes sense to charge for the system prompt after every agent turn if the LLM is only pausing for a fraction of a second while waiting for a tool function result.
              This is overlooking some details, like how it takes output tokens to call a tool, and the tool function result still needs to be processed as input tokens. But in my case,
              the api cost is dominated by the large system prompt being charged as cached input tokens after every agent turn.
            </p>
            <p>
              The pricing for an agent loop is understandable when your application code has the agent loop, and is making a new api call after each tool call.
              But it makes even less sense when you provide a remote MCP server and do not handle the agent loop yourself. OpenAI handles it correctly.
              A single api call to OpenAI with a remote MCP server will only ever charge you for the input prompt once. An Anthropic api call with remote MCP
              server, however, works like the previous example.
            </p>
            <p>
              Some real numbers, the gpt-5.5 (medium) benchmark had an average input tokens per magic turn of 11,386. The average for claude-fable-5 (medium) was 51,610.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="article-body-section">
            <h2>Title</h2>
            <p>
              Put explanation text here.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="article-body-section">
            <h2>Title</h2>
            <p>
              Put explanation text here.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="article-body-section">
            <h2>Title</h2>
            <p>
              Put explanation text here.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="article-body-section">
            <h2>Why Opus 4.8 performed poorly</h2>
            <p>
              put explanation text here. Look at
              <a
                href="https://app.mtgautodeck.com/public/benchmarks/6349dda2-4069-4825-971e-8c11234260c4?simulation=14d0d2df-c5af-4c78-83ed-6131ff589b34&run=ad893839-5bbd-4695-8fe2-1a3e80d0dd8b&turn=1"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noreferrer noopener">this example</a
              >.
            </p>
          </section>

          <!-- <section class="benchmark-chart-section">
            <h2 class="benchmark-chart-heading">
              Reasoning tokens per turn
              <span>(lower is better) - click on bar to view simulations</span>
            </h2>
            <div
              class="benchmark-chart-viewport"
              data-mtg-bench-chart-viewport
            >
              <div
                class="benchmark-score-chart benchmark-chart-scale-frame"
                data-mtg-bench-reasoning-chart
                role="group"
                aria-label="Reasoning tokens per turn by benchmark, lower is better"
              ></div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section class="article-body-section">
            <h2>Token efficiency</h2>
            <p>
              Token efficiency explanation.
            </p>
          </section> -->
        </div>
      </article>
    </main>

    <footer class="site-footer" aria-label="Footer">
      <div class="footer-content">
        <a class="text-link footer-brand" href="/">MTG Auto Deck</a>
        <a
          class="text-link"
          href={contactUrl}>{contactEmail}</a
        >
      </div>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>

<script>
  import mtgBenchResultsData from "../../data/mtg-bench-results.json"

  type MtgBenchResultEntry = {
    benchmarkId: string
    publicBenchmarkUrl: string
    model: string | null
    providerKey: string | null
    reasoningEffort: string | null
    mtgAutoDeckScore: number | null
    reasoningTokensPerAttemptedTurn: number | null
    displayedCostPerAttemptedTurn: number | null
    scatterLabelPosition?: string | null
    hideReasoningEffortOnScatterLabel?: boolean | null
  }

  type MtgBenchScatterLabelPosition =
    | "right"
    | "left"
    | "top"
    | "bottom"
    | "bottom-left"
    | "bottom-right"
    | "top-left"
    | "top-right"

  type MtgBenchResultsData = {
    schemaVersion: number
    generatedAt: string
    benchmarks: MtgBenchResultEntry[]
  }

  type MtgBenchResultsState = {
    status: "loaded"
    schemaVersion: number
    benchmarkIds: string[]
    results: MtgBenchResultEntry[]
    resultsByBenchmarkId: Record<string, MtgBenchResultEntry>
    loadedAt: string
  }

  type MtgBenchMetricBar = {
    benchmarkId: string
    publicBenchmarkUrl: string
    labelLineOne: string
    labelLineTwo: string
    metricAriaLabel: string
    providerMatch: MtgBenchProviderMatch | null
    value: number | null
    valueLabel: string
    heightPercent: number
  }

  type MtgBenchScatterPoint = {
    benchmarkId: string
    publicBenchmarkUrl: string
    costPerAttemptedTurn: number
    costLabel: string
    modelLabel: string
    reasoningEffortLabel: string
    labelPosition: MtgBenchScatterLabelPosition
    hideReasoningEffortOnLabel: boolean
    score: number
    scoreLabel: string
    providerMatch: MtgBenchProviderMatch | null
  }

  type MtgBenchProviderMatch = {
    barColor: string
    barTextColor: string
    logoAlt: string
    logoSrc: string
  }

  const mtgBenchProviderMatches: Record<string, MtgBenchProviderMatch> = {
    alibaba: {
      barColor: "#FF7018",
      barTextColor: "#ffffff",
      logoAlt: "Alibaba",
      logoSrc: "/alibaba_small.svg",
    },
    anthropic: {
      barColor: "#CC785C",
      barTextColor: "#ffffff",
      logoAlt: "Anthropic",
      logoSrc: "/anthropic-1.svg",
    },
    deepseek: {
      barColor: "#2243E6",
      barTextColor: "#ffffff",
      logoAlt: "DeepSeek",
      logoSrc: "/deepseek_small.svg",
    },
    google: {
      barColor: "#4890E5",
      barTextColor: "#ffffff",
      logoAlt: "Google",
      logoSrc: "/google_small.svg",
    },
    moonshotai: {
      barColor: "#047AFE",
      barTextColor: "#ffffff",
      logoAlt: "Kimi",
      logoSrc: "/kimi_small.png",
    },
    openai: {
      barColor: "#10A37F",
      barTextColor: "#ffffff",
      logoAlt: "OpenAI",
      logoSrc: "/openai_small.svg",
    },
    xai: {
      barColor: "#736CD3",
      barTextColor: "#ffffff",
      logoAlt: "xAI",
      logoSrc: "/xai.svg",
    },
  }
  const mtgBenchScatterMaxCostUsd = 0.3
  const mtgBenchScatterCostTicks = [0, 0.05, 0.1, 0.15, 0.2, 0.25, 0.3]
  const mtgBenchScatterScoreTicks = [0, 25, 50, 75, 100]
  const mtgBenchScatterLabelPositions = new Set<string>([
    "right",
    "left",
    "top",
    "bottom",
    "bottom-left",
    "bottom-right",
    "top-left",
    "top-right",
  ])
  const mtgBenchResultsPayload =
    mtgBenchResultsData as MtgBenchResultsData
  const mtgBenchResults = mtgBenchResultsPayload.benchmarks
  const mtgBenchBenchmarkIds = mtgBenchResults.map(
    (result) => result.benchmarkId
  )
  const mtgBenchResultsByBenchmarkId = Object.fromEntries(
    mtgBenchResults.map((result) => [result.benchmarkId, result])
  ) as Record<string, MtgBenchResultEntry>
  const mtgBenchWindow = window as Window & {
    mtgBenchResults: MtgBenchResultsState
  }
  const mtgBenchScoreChart = document.querySelector<HTMLElement>(
    "[data-mtg-bench-score-chart]"
  )
  const mtgBenchReasoningChart = document.querySelector<HTMLElement>(
    "[data-mtg-bench-reasoning-chart]"
  )
  const mtgBenchCostScoreChart = document.querySelector<HTMLElement>(
    "[data-mtg-bench-cost-score-chart]"
  )
  const mtgBenchChartViewports = [
    ...document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>(
      "[data-mtg-bench-chart-viewport]"
    ),
  ]

  mtgBenchWindow.mtgBenchResults = {
    status: "loaded",
    schemaVersion: mtgBenchResultsPayload.schemaVersion,
    benchmarkIds: [...mtgBenchBenchmarkIds],
    results: mtgBenchResults,
    resultsByBenchmarkId: mtgBenchResultsByBenchmarkId,
    loadedAt: mtgBenchResultsPayload.generatedAt,
  }

  renderMtgBenchMetricChart(
    mtgBenchScoreChart,
    buildMtgBenchScoreBars(mtgBenchResults)
  )
  renderMtgBenchMetricChart(
    mtgBenchReasoningChart,
    buildMtgBenchReasoningTokenBars(mtgBenchResults)
  )
  renderMtgBenchScatterChart(
    mtgBenchCostScoreChart,
    buildMtgBenchCostScorePoints(mtgBenchResults)
  )
  setupMtgBenchChartViewports(mtgBenchChartViewports)

  function buildMtgBenchScoreBars(results: readonly MtgBenchResultEntry[]) {
    return results
      .map((result) => {
        const labelLines = buildMtgBenchLabelLines(
          getMtgBenchModelLabel(result),
          getMtgBenchReasoningEffortLabel(result)
        )
        const score = getMtgBenchScore(result)

        return {
          benchmarkId: result.benchmarkId,
          publicBenchmarkUrl: result.publicBenchmarkUrl,
          labelLineOne: labelLines[0],
          labelLineTwo: labelLines[1],
          metricAriaLabel: "Overall Score, higher is better",
          providerMatch: getMtgBenchProviderMatch(result),
          value: score,
          valueLabel: formatMtgBenchBarScore(score),
          heightPercent: Math.max(0, Math.min(score ?? 0, 100)),
        }
      })
      .sort(compareMtgBenchScoreBars)
  }

  function buildMtgBenchReasoningTokenBars(
    results: readonly MtgBenchResultEntry[]
  ) {
    const maxReasoningTokens = Math.max(
      0,
      ...results
        .map((result) => getMtgBenchReasoningTokensPerTurn(result))
        .filter((value): value is number => value !== null)
    )

    return results
      .map((result) => {
        const reasoningTokens = getMtgBenchReasoningTokensPerTurn(result)
        const labelLines = buildMtgBenchLabelLines(
          getMtgBenchModelLabel(result),
          getMtgBenchReasoningEffortLabel(result)
        )

        return {
          benchmarkId: result.benchmarkId,
          publicBenchmarkUrl: result.publicBenchmarkUrl,
          labelLineOne: labelLines[0],
          labelLineTwo: labelLines[1],
          metricAriaLabel: "Reasoning tokens per turn, lower is better",
          providerMatch: getMtgBenchProviderMatch(result),
          value: reasoningTokens,
          valueLabel: formatMtgBenchBarTokenRate(reasoningTokens),
          heightPercent:
            maxReasoningTokens > 0 && reasoningTokens !== null
              ? (reasoningTokens / maxReasoningTokens) * 100
              : 0,
        }
      })
      .sort(compareMtgBenchReasoningTokenBars)
  }

  function buildMtgBenchCostScorePoints(
    results: readonly MtgBenchResultEntry[]
  ) {
    return results.flatMap((result) => {
      const costPerAttemptedTurn = getMtgBenchCostPerAttemptedTurn(result)
      const score = getMtgBenchScore(result)

      if (costPerAttemptedTurn === null || score === null) {
        return []
      }

      return [
        {
          benchmarkId: result.benchmarkId,
          publicBenchmarkUrl: result.publicBenchmarkUrl,
          costPerAttemptedTurn,
          costLabel: formatMtgBenchScatterPointCost(costPerAttemptedTurn),
          modelLabel: getMtgBenchModelLabel(result),
          reasoningEffortLabel: getMtgBenchReasoningEffortLabel(result),
          labelPosition: getMtgBenchScatterLabelPosition(result),
          hideReasoningEffortOnLabel:
            getMtgBenchHideReasoningEffortOnScatterLabel(result),
          score,
          scoreLabel: formatMtgBenchBarScore(score),
          providerMatch: getMtgBenchProviderMatch(result),
        },
      ]
    })
  }

  function compareMtgBenchScoreBars(
    first: MtgBenchMetricBar,
    second: MtgBenchMetricBar
  ) {
    const firstScore = first.value ?? Number.NEGATIVE_INFINITY
    const secondScore = second.value ?? Number.NEGATIVE_INFINITY
    const scoreCompare = secondScore - firstScore

    return scoreCompare || first.benchmarkId.localeCompare(second.benchmarkId)
  }

  function compareMtgBenchReasoningTokenBars(
    first: MtgBenchMetricBar,
    second: MtgBenchMetricBar
  ) {
    const firstTokens = first.value ?? Number.POSITIVE_INFINITY
    const secondTokens = second.value ?? Number.POSITIVE_INFINITY
    const tokenCompare = firstTokens - secondTokens

    return tokenCompare || first.benchmarkId.localeCompare(second.benchmarkId)
  }

  function renderMtgBenchMetricChart(
    chart: HTMLElement | null,
    metricBars: readonly MtgBenchMetricBar[]
  ) {
    if (!chart) {
      return
    }

    chart.replaceChildren(
      ...metricBars.map((metricBar) => {
        const column = document.createElement("a")
        const plot = document.createElement("div")
        const bar = document.createElement("div")
        const logoSlot = document.createElement("div")
        const label = document.createElement("div")
        const labelText = document.createElement("div")
        const modelLabel = document.createElement("span")
        const reasoningEffortLabel = document.createElement("span")

        column.className = "benchmark-score-column"
        column.href = metricBar.publicBenchmarkUrl
        column.rel = "noreferrer noopener"
        column.target = "_blank"
        column.setAttribute(
          "aria-label",
          `Open benchmark ${metricBar.labelLineOne} ${metricBar.labelLineTwo}, ${metricBar.metricAriaLabel} ${metricBar.valueLabel}`
        )
        plot.className = "benchmark-score-plot"
        bar.className = "benchmark-score-bar"
        bar.style.height = `${Math.max(
          0,
          Math.min(metricBar.heightPercent, 100)
        )}%`
        if (metricBar.providerMatch) {
          bar.style.backgroundColor = metricBar.providerMatch.barColor
          bar.style.color = metricBar.providerMatch.barTextColor
        }
        bar.textContent = metricBar.valueLabel
        bar.setAttribute(
          "aria-label",
          `${metricBar.metricAriaLabel} ${metricBar.valueLabel}`
        )
        logoSlot.className = "benchmark-score-logo-slot"
        if (metricBar.providerMatch) {
          const logo = document.createElement("img")

          logo.alt = metricBar.providerMatch.logoAlt
          logo.className = "benchmark-score-logo"
          logo.decoding = "async"
          logo.loading = "lazy"
          logo.src = metricBar.providerMatch.logoSrc
          logoSlot.append(logo)
        }
        label.className = "benchmark-score-label"
        labelText.className = "benchmark-score-label-text"
        modelLabel.textContent = metricBar.labelLineOne
        reasoningEffortLabel.textContent = metricBar.labelLineTwo

        labelText.append(modelLabel, reasoningEffortLabel)
        label.append(labelText)
        plot.append(bar)
        column.append(plot, logoSlot, label)

        return column
      })
    )
  }

  function renderMtgBenchScatterChart(
    chart: HTMLElement | null,
    points: readonly MtgBenchScatterPoint[]
  ) {
    if (!chart) {
      return
    }

    const layout = document.createElement("div")
    const plot = document.createElement("div")
    const pointLayer = document.createElement("div")
    const yAxisLabel = document.createElement("span")
    const xAxisLabel = document.createElement("span")
    const yTickLabels = mtgBenchScatterScoreTicks.map((tick) => {
      const tickLabel = document.createElement("span")

      tickLabel.className =
        "benchmark-scatter-axis-label benchmark-scatter-y-tick"
      tickLabel.style.bottom = `${getMtgBenchScatterScorePercent(tick)}%`
      tickLabel.textContent = String(tick)

      return tickLabel
    })
    const xTickLabels = mtgBenchScatterCostTicks.map((tick) => {
      const tickLabel = document.createElement("span")

      tickLabel.className =
        "benchmark-scatter-axis-label benchmark-scatter-x-tick"
      tickLabel.style.left = `${getMtgBenchScatterCostPercent(tick)}%`
      tickLabel.textContent = formatMtgBenchScatterCostTick(tick)

      return tickLabel
    })

    layout.className = "benchmark-scatter-layout"
    plot.className = "benchmark-scatter-plot"
    pointLayer.className = "benchmark-scatter-point-layer"
    yAxisLabel.className =
      "benchmark-scatter-axis-title benchmark-scatter-y-title"
    xAxisLabel.className =
      "benchmark-scatter-axis-title benchmark-scatter-x-title"
    yAxisLabel.textContent = "Score"
    xAxisLabel.textContent = "Cost per attempted turn (USD)"

    pointLayer.append(
      ...points.map((point) => {
        const costPercent = getMtgBenchScatterCostPercent(
          point.costPerAttemptedTurn
        )
        const dot = document.createElement("a")
        const pointLabel = document.createElement("span")
        const tooltip = document.createElement("span")
        const tooltipHeader = document.createElement("span")
        const tooltipTitle = document.createElement("span")
        const tooltipReasoning = document.createElement("span")
        const tooltipStats = document.createElement("span")
        const scoreStat = document.createElement("span")
        const costStat = document.createElement("span")

        dot.className = "benchmark-scatter-point"
        if (costPercent < 28) {
          dot.classList.add("benchmark-scatter-point-right")
        } else if (costPercent > 72) {
          dot.classList.add("benchmark-scatter-point-left")
        }
        dot.href = point.publicBenchmarkUrl
        dot.rel = "noreferrer noopener"
        dot.target = "_blank"
        dot.setAttribute(
          "aria-label",
          `Open benchmark for ${point.modelLabel}, ${point.reasoningEffortLabel} reasoning effort, score ${point.scoreLabel}, cost per attempted turn ${point.costLabel}`
        )
        dot.style.left = `${costPercent}%`
        dot.style.bottom = `${getMtgBenchScatterScorePercent(point.score)}%`
        dot.style.backgroundColor =
          point.providerMatch?.barColor ?? "var(--accent-strong)"

        pointLabel.className = `benchmark-scatter-point-label benchmark-scatter-point-label-${point.labelPosition}`
        pointLabel.setAttribute("aria-hidden", "true")
        renderMtgBenchScatterPointLabel(pointLabel, point)

        tooltip.className = "benchmark-scatter-tooltip"
        tooltip.setAttribute("aria-hidden", "true")
        tooltipHeader.className = "benchmark-scatter-tooltip-header"
        tooltipTitle.className = "benchmark-scatter-tooltip-title"
        tooltipReasoning.className = "benchmark-scatter-tooltip-muted"
        tooltipStats.className = "benchmark-scatter-tooltip-stats"
        tooltipTitle.textContent = point.modelLabel
        tooltipReasoning.textContent = point.reasoningEffortLabel
        scoreStat.textContent = `Score ${point.scoreLabel}`
        costStat.textContent = `Cost ${point.costLabel}`

        if (point.providerMatch) {
          const logo = document.createElement("img")

          logo.alt = point.providerMatch.logoAlt
          logo.className = "benchmark-scatter-tooltip-logo"
          logo.decoding = "async"
          logo.loading = "lazy"
          logo.src = point.providerMatch.logoSrc
          tooltipHeader.append(logo)
        }

        tooltipHeader.append(tooltipTitle)
        tooltipStats.append(scoreStat, costStat)
        tooltip.append(tooltipHeader, tooltipReasoning, tooltipStats)
        dot.append(pointLabel, tooltip)

        return dot
      })
    )
    plot.append(pointLayer, ...yTickLabels, ...xTickLabels, xAxisLabel)
    layout.append(yAxisLabel, plot)

    chart.replaceChildren(layout)
  }

  function setupMtgBenchChartViewports(
    viewports: readonly HTMLElement[]
  ) {
    const updateViewport = (viewport: HTMLElement) => {
      const chart = viewport.firstElementChild

      if (!(chart instanceof HTMLElement)) {
        return
      }

      const availableWidth = viewport.clientWidth
      const chartWidth = chart.offsetWidth
      const chartHeight = chart.offsetHeight

      if (availableWidth <= 0 || chartWidth <= 0 || chartHeight <= 0) {
        return
      }

      const chartScale = Math.min(1, availableWidth / chartWidth)

      viewport.style.setProperty(
        "--benchmark-chart-scale",
        chartScale.toFixed(4)
      )
      viewport.style.setProperty(
        "--benchmark-chart-scaled-height",
        `${Math.ceil(chartHeight * chartScale)}px`
      )
    }
    const updateViewports = () => {
      viewports.forEach(updateViewport)
    }

    if (viewports.length === 0) {
      return
    }

    requestAnimationFrame(updateViewports)
    window.addEventListener("load", updateViewports, { once: true })

    if ("ResizeObserver" in window) {
      const resizeObserver = new ResizeObserver(updateViewports)

      viewports.forEach((viewport) => resizeObserver.observe(viewport))
      return
    }

    window.addEventListener("resize", updateViewports)
  }

  function getMtgBenchScore(result: MtgBenchResultEntry) {
    const score = result.mtgAutoDeckScore

    return typeof score === "number" && Number.isFinite(score) ? score : null
  }

  function getMtgBenchReasoningTokensPerTurn(result: MtgBenchResultEntry) {
    const reasoningTokens = result.reasoningTokensPerAttemptedTurn

    return typeof reasoningTokens === "number" &&
      Number.isFinite(reasoningTokens)
      ? reasoningTokens
      : null
  }

  function getMtgBenchCostPerAttemptedTurn(result: MtgBenchResultEntry) {
    const costPerAttemptedTurn = result.displayedCostPerAttemptedTurn

    if (
      typeof costPerAttemptedTurn !== "number" ||
      !Number.isFinite(costPerAttemptedTurn)
    ) {
      return null
    }

    return costPerAttemptedTurn
  }

  function getMtgBenchScatterLabelPosition(
    result: MtgBenchResultEntry
  ): MtgBenchScatterLabelPosition {
    const labelPosition =
      typeof result.scatterLabelPosition === "string"
        ? result.scatterLabelPosition.trim().toLowerCase()
        : ""

    return mtgBenchScatterLabelPositions.has(labelPosition)
      ? (labelPosition as MtgBenchScatterLabelPosition)
      : "right"
  }

  function getMtgBenchHideReasoningEffortOnScatterLabel(
    result: MtgBenchResultEntry
  ) {
    return result.hideReasoningEffortOnScatterLabel === true
  }

  function renderMtgBenchScatterPointLabel(
    label: HTMLElement,
    point: MtgBenchScatterPoint
  ) {
    const modelLabel = document.createElement("span")

    modelLabel.className = "benchmark-scatter-point-label-model"
    modelLabel.textContent = point.modelLabel
    label.append(modelLabel)

    if (point.hideReasoningEffortOnLabel) {
      return
    }

    const reasoningEffortLabel = document.createElement("span")

    reasoningEffortLabel.className =
      "benchmark-scatter-point-label-reasoning"
    reasoningEffortLabel.textContent = ` (${point.reasoningEffortLabel})`
    label.append(reasoningEffortLabel)
  }

  function getMtgBenchProviderMatch(result: MtgBenchResultEntry) {
    const providerKey =
      typeof result.providerKey === "string"
        ? result.providerKey.trim().toLowerCase()
        : ""

    return providerKey ? (mtgBenchProviderMatches[providerKey] ?? null) : null
  }

  function getMtgBenchModelLabel(result: MtgBenchResultEntry) {
    const model = result.model

    if (typeof model !== "string") {
      return "-"
    }

    const trimmedModel = model.trim()

    if (!trimmedModel) {
      return "-"
    }

    const slashIndex = trimmedModel.indexOf("/")
    const modelWithoutProvider =
      slashIndex === -1 ? trimmedModel : trimmedModel.slice(slashIndex + 1)

    return modelWithoutProvider.trim() || trimmedModel
  }

  function getMtgBenchReasoningEffortLabel(result: MtgBenchResultEntry) {
    const reasoningEffort = result.reasoningEffort

    return typeof reasoningEffort === "string" && reasoningEffort.trim()
      ? reasoningEffort.trim().replaceAll("_", " ")
      : "-"
  }

  function buildMtgBenchLabelLines(
    modelLabel: string,
    reasoningEffortLabel: string
  ): [string, string] {
    const modelSplit = getMtgBenchModelLabelSplit(modelLabel)

    if (!modelSplit) {
      return [modelLabel, reasoningEffortLabel]
    }

    return [
      modelSplit[0],
      [modelSplit[1], reasoningEffortLabel].filter(Boolean).join(" "),
    ]
  }

  function getMtgBenchModelLabelSplit(modelLabel: string) {
    if (modelLabel.length < 16) {
      return null
    }

    const preferredDashIndex = modelLabel.lastIndexOf("-", 15)
    const dashIndex =
      preferredDashIndex === -1
        ? modelLabel.indexOf("-")
        : preferredDashIndex

    if (dashIndex === -1 || dashIndex === modelLabel.length - 1) {
      return null
    }

    return [
      modelLabel.slice(0, dashIndex + 1),
      modelLabel.slice(dashIndex + 1),
    ] as const
  }

  function formatMtgBenchBarScore(score: number | null) {
    return score === null ? "-" : score.toFixed(1).replace(/\.0$/u, "")
  }

  function formatMtgBenchBarTokenRate(tokenRate: number | null) {
    return tokenRate === null ? "-" : `${(tokenRate / 1000).toFixed(1)}K`
  }

  function getMtgBenchScatterCostPercent(costPerAttemptedTurn: number) {
    return clampMtgBenchPercent(
      (costPerAttemptedTurn / mtgBenchScatterMaxCostUsd) * 100
    )
  }

  function getMtgBenchScatterScorePercent(score: number) {
    return clampMtgBenchPercent(score)
  }

  function clampMtgBenchPercent(percent: number) {
    return Math.round(Math.max(0, Math.min(percent, 100)) * 1000) / 1000
  }

  function formatMtgBenchScatterCostTick(costUsd: number) {
    return `$${costUsd.toFixed(2)}`
  }

  function formatMtgBenchScatterPointCost(costUsd: number) {
    const roundedCostLabel = costUsd.toFixed(2)

    return costUsd > 0 && roundedCostLabel === "0.00"
      ? "$0.01"
      : `$${roundedCostLabel}`
  }
</script>

